---
const withBase = (path: string) => {
  const base = '/arcup';
  if (path === '/') return `${base}/`;
  return `${base}${path}`;
};
---

<main id="main-content" class="page-shell page-join" aria-labelledby="join-title">
  
  <!-- HERO -->
  <header class="join-hero" aria-labelledby="join-title">
    <h1 id="join-title">Join Arc^</h1>
    <p class="join-lede">Arc^ is a framework for building technology differently. Whether you're a student, researcher, builder, or community partner ‚Äî if you're ready to work openly and ethically, there's a place for you here.</p>
  </header>

  <!-- ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS SECTION -->
  <section class="acknowledgements-section surface-panel" aria-labelledby="acknowledgements-heading">
    <h2 id="acknowledgements-heading">Standing on Shoulders</h2>
    
    <div class="acknowledgements-intro">
      <p>Arc^ exists because others paved the way. We're stronger together.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="acknowledgements-grid">
      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_science" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3>Open Science Pioneers</h3>
        <p>Those who fought for open access, preprints, and transparent peer review.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Traditional_ecological_knowledge" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3>Indigenous Knowledge Keepers</h3>
        <p>Stewarding ecological wisdom for generations, often without recognition or recompense.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Citizen_science" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3>Community Scientists</h3>
        <p>Everyday people advancing knowledge without institutional backing.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_hardware" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3>Open Hardware Builders</h3>
        <p>Engineers sharing schematics freely so others can repair, modify, and improve.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Copyleft" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3>Copyleft Advocates</h3>
        <p>Creators who chose to keep knowledge in the commons rather than lock it away.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Environmental_defender" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3>Environmental Defenders</h3>
        <p>Those who risk everything to protect land, water, and life itself.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GETTING STARTED -->
  <div class="section-divider" aria-hidden="true">
    <span class="divider-label">getting started</span>
  </div>

  <section class="join-getting-started surface-panel">
    <h2>Getting Started</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">New to Arc^ or plasma research? Start here:</p>
    
    <div class="getting-started-grid">
      <article class="start-card">
        <span class="start-number">01</span>
        <h3>Read the Framework</h3>
        <p>Understand RE:TECH principles and how Arc^ approaches research differently.</p>
        <a href={withBase("/how")} class="button button-outline">Explore How We Work</a>
      </article>

      <article class="start-card">
        <span class="start-number">02</span>
        <h3>Browse Projects</h3>
        <p>Find a project that matches your interests or skills. Start with replication tasks.</p>
        <a href={withBase("/projects")} class="button button-outline">View Active Projects</a>
      </article>

      <article class="start-card">
        <span class="start-number">03</span>
        <h3>Reach Out</h3>
        <p>Contact Ali to discuss how you'd like to contribute. No formal credentials required.</p>
        <a href="mailto:ali@xbyali.page?subject=Joining%20Arc^" class="button button-outline">Get in Touch</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WAYS TO CONTRIBUTE -->
  <div class="section-divider" aria-hidden="true">
    <span class="divider-label">ways to contribute</span>
  </div>

  <section class="contribute-section">
    <header class="section-header">
      <h2>How You Can Contribute</h2>
      <p class="lead">Arc^ needs diverse skills and perspectives. Find the path that fits you.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="contribute-grid">
      <article class="contribute-card surface-panel">
        <div class="card-icon">üî¨</div>
        <h3>Research Contributors</h3>
        <p>Help advance plasma science through replication, analysis, and documentation.</p>
        <ul class="contribute-tasks">
          <li>Replicate existing protocols</li>
          <li>Review literature and methods</li>
          <li>Analyze open datasets</li>
          <li>Document experimental procedures</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="ideal-for"><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Students, independent researchers, scientists, data analysts</p>
        <a href="mailto:ali@xbyali.page?subject=Research%20Contribution" class="button">Express Interest</a>
      </article>

      <article class="contribute-card surface-panel">
        <div class="card-icon">üõ†Ô∏è</div>
        <h3>Technical Contributors</h3>
        <p>Build open hardware, improve documentation, or develop tools for collaborative research.</p>
        <ul class="contribute-tasks">
          <li>Design plasma device components</li>
          <li>Create CAD files and build guides</li>
          <li>Write safety documentation</li>
          <li>Develop testing frameworks</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="ideal-for"><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Engineers, makers, technical writers, developers</p>
        <a href="mailto:ali@xbyali.page?subject=Technical%20Contribution" class="button">Express Interest</a>
      </article>

      <article class="contribute-card surface-panel">
        <div class="card-icon">üåç</div>
        <h3>Community Partners</h3>
        <p>Co-design research with communities facing environmental challenges.</p>
        <ul class="contribute-tasks">
          <li>Identify local restoration needs</li>
          <li>Test protocols in real contexts</li>
          <li>Share traditional ecological knowledge</li>
          <li>Guide ethical research practices</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="ideal-for"><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Community organizers, farmers, environmental groups, land stewards</p>
        <a href="mailto:ali@xbyali.page?subject=Community%20Partnership" class="button">Express Interest</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- EXPECTATIONS -->
  <div class="section-divider" aria-hidden="true">
    <span class="divider-label">what to expect</span>
  </div>

  <section class="expectations-section">
    <header class="section-header">
      <h2>What to Expect</h2>
      <p class="lead">Arc^ is transparent about how we work. Here's what collaboration looks like.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="expectations-grid">
      <article class="expectation-card surface-panel">
        <h3>Open by Default</h3>
        <p>Your work will be public from the start. Protocols, data, and findings are shared openly under open licenses (CC BY-NC-SA, CERN OHL-S, AGPL-3.0).</p>
      </article>

      <article class="expectation-card surface-panel">
        <h3>Credit & Attribution</h3>
        <p>All contributors are named and credited. Your contributions matter and will be acknowledged publicly in outputs and documentation.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="expectation-card surface-panel">
        <h3>Iterative & Imperfect</h3>
        <p>We document mistakes openly. Early-stage work is messy ‚Äî that's normal and expected. Progress over perfection.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="expectation-card surface-panel">
        <h3>Community-Led Governance</h3>
        <p>As Arc^ grows, governance structures will be co-designed with contributors. Right now, Ali is the primary steward, but that will evolve.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <div class="section-divider" aria-hidden="true">
    <span class="divider-label">common questions</span>
  </div>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    
    <div class="faq-list">
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do I need a degree or formal credentials?</h3>
        <p>No. Arc^ values curiosity, rigor, and care over credentials. If you're willing to learn, document thoroughly, and work ethically, you're welcome.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="faq-item">
        <h3>Is this volunteer-only or can I get paid?</h3>
        <p>Currently, Arc^ is volunteer-led. As the framework grows and funding models develop, paid roles may emerge ‚Äî but they'll prioritize community benefit over profit.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I use Arc^ research commercially?</h3>
        <p>Yes, but with constraints. Non-commercial use is open. Commercial use requires benefit-sharing agreements that return value to the commons. Contact Ali to discuss.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="faq-item">
        <h3>How does Arc^ handle intellectual property?</h3>
        <p>Knowledge stays in the commons. Documentation is CC BY-NC-SA, hardware is CERN OHL-S, software is AGPL-3.0, and data is ODC-BY or CC BY-SA. No patents.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="faq-item">
        <h3>What if I disagree with a decision?</h3>
        <p>Arc^ is building governance structures as it grows. Right now, concerns should be raised directly with Ali. As the community expands, more formal dispute resolution processes will be co-designed.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FINAL CTA -->
  <div class="section-divider" aria-hidden="true">
    <span class="divider-label">ready to begin?</span>
  </div>

  <section class="final-cta surface-panel">
    <h2>Ready to Begin?</h2>
    <p>The best way to start is to reach out. Share what interests you, what skills you bring, and how you'd like to contribute. No formal applications ‚Äî just a conversation.</p>
    <a href="mailto:ali@xbyali.page?subject=Ready%20to%20Join%20Arc^" class="button">Contact Ali</a>
  </section>

</main>